{"questionId":"12990","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the functions <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n</math></span> defined by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = {\\text{ln}}\\left| x \\right|\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> \\ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left\\{ 0 \\right\\}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>{</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>}</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = {\\text{ln}}\\left| {x + k} \\right|\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> \\ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left\\{ { - k} \\right\\}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>{</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>}</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k > 2\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Describe the transformation by which <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\"> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span> is transformed to <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right)\"> <mi>g</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p>\n<p>translation <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"> <mi>k</mi> </math></span> units to the left (or equivalent) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12990","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ2.H_11a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Describe the transformation by which f ( x ) is transformed to g ( x ) .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.11—Transformation of functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.14—Odd and even functions, self-inverse, inverse and domain restriction","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.16—Graphing modulus equations and inequalities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}